channel.title: Cannot connect to my server through my client.. [PI] 317
channel.description:
I'm having trouble with making it so people can connect to my server.. I've done everything exactly. My port is forwarded through uTorrent, and through Simple Port Forwarding tool. I cannot connect to my server through my client. I tried, got an error message, so I thought I had messed up some vital piece of code; I re-extracted my Client folder, resetting everything, changed the Compiler to my Java version again, FOUND CLIENT.JAVA; I opened it up in Notepad ++, searched "server =", found "Server = 127.0.0.0"; Changed that to "Server =kleberscape.no-ip.org". I compiled. Tried running the server again, opened my client, tried connecting, and I still get the error message... I also tried to do it with the IP shown on IP CHICKEN, and it still doesn't worked. Recompiled as normal, Client still shows "error connecting to server". I have NO-IP DUC running, my port 43594 is shown as OPEN wherever I check it, no matter what site it is that checks my port, it still says open. I'm not stupid, although I'm thinking I missed something absurdly simple... What's my problem here??? :confused: :confused: :confused:
[img]http://img6.imageshack.us/img6/1256/helppm.jpg[/img]
